sec.p:
Volunteers applied the appropriated DDMNs on the designated clean and dry studied area by themselves. DDMN patch was applied daily before bedtime for 4 weeks. During the entire study period, volunteers had normal routine of skin cleansing and makeup. Personal and medical history was obtained at baseline. Colorimeter (DSMIII ColorMeter, Cortex technology, Denmark) was used to assess melanin index and luminance (L*) at week 0 (baseline), 1, 2, 3 and 4. Melanin index represents skin darkness with scale of 0 (white) to 100 (total black). The L* represents skin lightness with scale of 0 (total black) to 100 (white). The % change of melanin index and % change of L* were calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\% {\text{ Change of melanin index }} = \, \left[ {\left( {{\text{melanin index Wt }}{-}{\text{ melanin index W}}0} \right)/{\text{melanin index W}}0} \right)] \times {1}00,$$\end{document}%Change of melanin index=melanin index Wt-melanin index W0/melanin index W0]×100,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\% {\text{ Change of L}}^{*} \, = \, \left[ {\left( {{\text{L}}^{*} {\text{ Wt }}{-}{\text{ L}}^{*} {\text{ W}}0} \right)/{\text{ L}}^{*} {\text{ W}}0} \right)] \times {1}00,$$\end{document}%Change of L∗=L∗Wt-L∗W0/L∗W0]×100,where W0 = week 0, Wt = week of the measurement.
